  "prompt": "Indian Air Force: Can I stay with my family during the service after long hours of duty (daily) if not on leave?",
  "response": "In the Indian Air Force, the ability to stay with your family depends on several factors:\n\n1. Accommodation Options:\n- Married personnel posted at permanent stations can usually stay with family\n- Availability of family quarters/housing\n- Depends on specific station and rank\n\n2. Duty Constraints:\n- Long working hours are common\n- Some postings may have strict duty schedules\n- Emergency/operational requirements might limit family time\n\n3. Location Specific:\n- Peace stations generally allow more family interaction\n- Field/operational postings might have limited family proximity\n\n4. Factors Affecting Family Stay:\n- Rank\n- Type of posting\n- Station infrastructure\n- Availability of family accommodation\n- Current operational requirements\n\n5. Typical Scenarios:\n- Permanent/static stations: More likely to stay with family\n- Forward/operational bases: Limited family accommodation\n- Temporary postings: May require temporary separation\n\n6. Additional Considerations:\n- Periodic transfers\n- Postings in remote/strategic locations\n- Specific unit requirements\n\nWhile general policy supports family life, actual living arrangements depend on individual posting circumstances and operational needs.\n\nNote: Specific details can vary, so consulting IAF personnel or official guidelines is recommended.",
